# UGA Online GitHub (`uga-ool`)

Org repository list: **https://github.com/orgs/uga-ool/repositories**

## Repos and ownership

- Prefer **existing** `uga-ool` repos and patterns (Brightspace agents, Lit components, Kaltura tooling, React templates) before adding new dependencies or duplicate scaffolding.
- New apps that embed in **eLC** should align with **UGA Online** deployment expectations: course files, LTI, or documented AWS/API gateways per each repo’s README.

## Secrets and config

- **Never** commit API keys, OAuth client secrets, Kaltura admin secrets, or LLM keys. Use `.env` / `.env.local` (gitignored), CI secrets, or institutional secret stores.
- When copying from **DEVELOPER-GUIDE** or **AGENT-GUIDE** examples, strip real URLs and keys; use placeholders in issues and docs.

## Collaboration

- Use small, reviewable PRs; link eLC test plans or courses when behavior is LMS-specific.
- Keep **CHANGELOG** / release notes when shipping assets instructors rely on (bundles, zip layouts, Manage Files paths).
- PR playbook: `docs/cursor/pr-and-code-review.md`
- Cursor: skill `uga-online-pr-and-code-review`; commands `uga-online-pr-review`, `uga-online-pre-pr-check`
